30-Sep-2019 · How do I add cron job under Linux or UNIX like operating system?  Cron allows Linux and Unix users to run commands or scripts at a given date and time.  ... The cron service (daemon) runs in the background and constantly checks the /etc/crontab file, and /etc/cron.*/ directories.

@daily: Run once a day, “0 0 * * *”
@hourly: Run once an hour, “0 * * * *”
@weekly: Run once a week, “0 0 * * 0”
@monthly: Run once a month, “0 0 1 * *”
